{
  "abstract": "Recent security challenges have caused disruption in the agricultural and economic livelihood of the people in north eastern states of Nigeria. However owing to recent gains in security and the resettlement of some displaced people agricultural activities have started coming back. A study was commissioned t asses the typology of farmers in the relatively safe local government areas of adamawa, Borno and Yobe States.",
